<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.2.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
      integrity="sha384-rbsA2VBKQhggwzxH7pPCaAqO46MgnOM80zW1RWuH61DGLwZJEdK2Kadq2F9CUG65"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/moreStyles.css" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.3/font/bootstrap-icons.css"
    />
    <title>About Me</title>
  </head>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #fff2f2;
      background-size: cover;
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      height: 100%;
    }
  </style>

  <body class="d-flex h-100 text-center">
    <div class="cover-container d-flex w-100 h-100 p-3 mx-auto flex-column">
      <%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>

      <main class="py-xxl-5 mb-xl-8 text-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto p-4 py-md-5 text-center">
          <h1 class="pb-3 mb-1 border-bottom">About me</h1>
          <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-md-flex justify-content-md-center">
            <button class="darkBtn" onclick="dark()">
              <i class="bi bi-moon moon"></i>
            </button>
          </div>

          <section class="py-5 text-center container">
            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-4 mx-auto">
              <img src="images/mecc.png" class="myself" alt="myself" />
            </div>
          </section>
          <p class="lead text-muted border-bottom">A little introduction...</p>
          <p class="fs-5 col-md-12 text-xl-start">
            My interest to code began when I was a superuser to manage a
            database. Since then, I have taken different coding courses and dip
            into learning new programming technique. After some time travelling
            and left London, I became a baker in Germany but then decided to
            take coding more seriously, so I completed the 6 months web
            development course with Hamburg Coding School. From then onwards,
            this website has evolved from testing backend data, until now, a bit
            more complex with a blog.
          </p>
          <p>
            There will be more features to be added. In so far, this has been my
            own personal project. There is a working blog and more advanced CSS.
            I hope to bring more animations and a map function in the coming
            future.
          </p>

          <div class="row align-content-center my-auto g-5">
            <div class="col-md-6 align-content-center">
              <div class="h-100 p-5 rounded-4 box1">
                <h2>What's Up?</h2>
                <p>
                  I am looking for a new start and to work as a junior web
                  developer. I'm working on mini-projects using Node.js,
                  React.js and Express.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="h-100 p-5 rounded-4 box2">
                <h2>Other Projects</h2>
                <p>
                  I have not deployed a lot of my projects as yet. But you can
                  find some of my mini projects on my Github account.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/SICelineChan/Project_cc_01"
                      >Travel blog</a
                    >
                    - my first travel blog using vanilla js
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>

      <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>
    </div>
    <script>
      function dark() {
        let element = document.body;
        element.classList.toggle("dark");
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
